6:
Sigh— Curry AGAIN? 
At least put some meat in it...
14:
With so many new mouths to feed, 
if you want expensive ingredients like 
meat, you'll have to save up for them 
yourself!
18:
Gotta bring home the bacon 'fore you 
can eat it, bro!
24: C-Claw?! When did you get here?!
28:
Just got here! Dude, it's been forever, 
man! How've you guys been?
37:
Hey, c'mon, bro, don't be like that. 
Turn that frown upside-down!
40:
Shouldn't you be off doin' your duties 
as chief of the catfolk?
44:
So THAT'S what was getting you. 
I've got it, bro, don't worry! 
But I'm glad you've got my back!
49:
Did your peace negotiations with 
the dogfolk work out?
52:
More or less, yeah, but there are still 
LOTS of problems to iron out.
55:
Figured I better expand my horizons, 
y'know? To really be a proper leader 
and stuff. That's where you guys come 
in!
60:
I see. You've come to Starview Village 
to study?
63:
Yeah! There's so much out there 
beyond my little corner of the world—
And it's my job now to learn about it!
66: Shall I escort you to the library, then?
71:
The library?! 
Dude, you guys have a library here!?
78:
WHOOOA! 
Man, just... just... just LOOK at all the 
books!
81:
Claw, please refrain from shouting in 
the library.
85:
I know, dude, but this is AWESOME! 
Are these seriously ALL library books?! 
I-is it really okay to borrow a few?
95:
Um, before you get TOO settled in 
reading, we should find you 
somewhere to stay. 
I'll show you around the village.
100:
Nah, don't sweat it. 
Man, I'd live riiight here if I could!
104: ...Living in the library is not permitted.
117:
Oh, I get it now. That's a good point! 
Let's see... Wow, check THAT out!
120: Does this guy EVER shut up?
124:
Sorry, sorry. 
I got a little carried away there, huh? 
There are so many cool books, 
I just couldn't help myself.
128:
Things aren't goin' as well as you let on, 
are they?
131: Well... You've got me there. Thanks to your guys' help, there haven't been any major conflicts, but...
132:
Just 'cause we've made peace with the 
dogfolk doesn't mean the people are 
prospering. The land's still as barren as 
ever.
134:
For now, my priority as chief is to make 
sure everyone at least gets hot meals 
in their bellies. So, here I am, hitting the 
books.
137:
So that's what you were up to. 
I guess I—
156:
Oh, right, I'm sorry, really! But check 
this book out! Look what it says here!
163:
It's got stuff about rocks and liquid 
gloop that burn like wood! 
Apparently they pack enough punch 
to power a windmill—without wind!
166:
Just imagine the impact on our forests 
if we could use this stuff to fuel the iron 
smelters instead of trees!
169:
To my recollection, internal 
combustion engines using similar 
energy sources are commonplace in 
the Endless Blue.
177: ...It would seem a field trip is in order.
185: Urgh, the sea always makes my fur feel gross.
190:
Who cares about FUR, bro? 
I'd shave myself into a naked mole-cat 
if I had to!
195:
I, I can't believe this place! 
Dude, they've got a whole entire CITY 
just floating on the water!
198:
We might have some of the flammable 
gloop they're using back in the 
canyon... right? 
Oh man, we GOTTA!
205:
...Really?! 
It's gonna CHANGE THE WORLD! 
It'll work, right?
209:
...If a bookworm like you thinks it'll work, 
I'm sure you'll figure somethin' out.
214:
...I will! I totally will, bro! 
I'll make a better world—
for catfolk AND dogfolk!
